Lucr. therefore seeks to maintain at the same time that cardinal point in the epicurean physics that atoms are impenetrable and indestructible‚ and yet possessed of weight shape and extension, and to shew how particles thus endowed are inca- pable of further division : atoms have parts, but these parts are minima, the ἐλάχιστα of Epicurus, not able to exist alone, abiding therefore in the atom from all eternity in unchangeable juxta-position.
